<DOC><DOCNO> AP890313-0097 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-13-89 1516EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Demjanjuk     03-13 0197</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Demjanjuk,0203</SECOND><HEAD>Holocaust Survivor Convicted of Attacking Demjanjuk Lawyer</HEAD><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Holocaust survivor was convicted Monday ofaggravated assault for hurling acid in the face of a lawyerrepresenting convicted Nazi war criminal John Demjanjuk.   Yisrael Yehezkieli, 70, was convicted after he confessed that hethrew acid in the face of Yoram Sheftel, Demjanjuk's defenseattorney, in December, Israel radio said.   The incident occurred during the funeral of another Demjanjukattorney, Dov Eitan, who committed suicide. A woman standing next toSheftel suffered minor injuries during the acid attack.   Yehezkieli will be sentenced May 4, the radio said. The crimecarries a maximum sentence of 20 years in jail.   Sheftel still suffers eye damage because of the attack. As aresult, the appeal in Demjanjuk's conviction and death penalty hasbeen postponed until November.   Demjanjuk, a 68-year-old Ohio autoworker, was sentenced to deathlast year for crimes against humanity and against the Jewish people.   He was convicted of being the guard ``Ivan the Terrible'' whooperated the gas chambers at the Treblinka death camp inGerman-occupied Poland in World War II. About 850,000 Jews werekilled in Treblinka, including most members of Yehezkieli's family.</TEXT></DOC>